{
  "stem": "12447.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People would throw out of the window a piece of bread, a scrap of a potato.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Later on, people did not-- the children would not ask for bread.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would ask like a little peels of potatoes-- if you can throw out of the window.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Or they stayed in the streets in groups of two or three and just begged, you know, if somebody could give them something to eat.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you could pass by maybe two, three days later.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the same children would be laying on the sidewalk already swollen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And a lot of them died.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there was, like, a group of people that were taking the dead people away on wagons and carrying them out from the ghetto into the cemetery, that they called it, the [NON-ENGLISH] Cemetery in Warsaw, a huge cemetery.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that cemetery was kind of separated from the main portion of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So they would let out the corpses to the cemetery, which was one of my escape routes also-- getting out into the cemetery, in through the cemetery, going out into the Aryan side.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I did all kinds of runs through the cemetery, getting over the cemetery.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was also a Polish cemetery on the other side.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a-- an area called [NON-ENGLISH], which was a field.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember there was, like, two or three holes from 1939 of the bombing of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were huge holes inside.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I had to kind of walk around these holes to get through there to the market.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was caught once over there and beaten up pretty bad from some Polacks that pulled my pants off and identified me that I was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
